<!-- A.2 -->
<div class='toload lemma'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Lemma A.2</span>
	Suppose $X$ and $Y$ are compact Hausdorff and $\psi:C(X,\mathbb{R})\to C(Y,\mathbb{R})$ is a bounded linear isomorphism. Then for any $x_0\in X$ and any $y_0\in Y$, $C(X,x_0,\mathbb{R})$ and $C(Y,y_0,\mathbb{R})$ are isomorphic as topological vector spaces.
	</p>
</div>